WEBVTT

00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:06.800
Hello and welcome back. In this practical, we will disable ASLR for the program we want to run.

00:00:09.140 --> 00:00:15.300
The easiest way to disable ASLR is not by doing it manually, but using DIE to do it for you.

00:00:19.010 --> 00:00:32.670
Let's load a CrackMe into DetectItEasy and then go to DIE. Go to the PE header, expand it,

00:00:32.670 --> 00:00:42.270
select optional header pull this down and then go to the dll characteristics

00:00:43.230 --> 00:00:52.190
click on flags drop down list. You need to uncheck dynamic base and high entropy va. But you cannot

00:00:52.190 --> 00:00:59.550
uncheck this because this is read only. So you have to uncheck the read only here and that allows you

00:00:59.550 --> 00:01:05.710
to uncheck this. The moment you uncheck this be careful, it will overwrite your original exe.

00:01:06.510 --> 00:01:11.790
But it will make a copy of it as a backup.

00:01:11.790 --> 00:01:13.610
Let me show you.

00:01:13.610 --> 00:01:20.950
When I uncheck this now, uncheck this immediately, you get a backup here, the backup file.

00:01:20.950 --> 00:01:22.310
See this?

00:01:22.310 --> 00:01:25.630
This is the backup and this one is overwritten.

00:01:25.630 --> 00:01:28.710
Alright, so now you can close.

00:01:28.710 --> 00:01:35.360
You don't need to click save.

00:01:35.360 --> 00:01:43.330
And now, when you load this new version and you open with DIE, and you go to the optional

00:01:43.330 --> 00:01:50.160
header and you pull this down, look at the DLL characteristics and you see

00:01:50.160 --> 00:02:01.230
dynamic base is unchecked. The final check. Now we want to run it with x64dbg

00:02:01.230 --> 00:02:16.120
and you see it works. It loads at the base address there. It shows you the base

00:02:16.120 --> 00:02:22.060
address rather than the ASLR randomized address. So that's all for this lesson.

00:02:22.060 --> 00:02:23.660
lesson. Thank you for watching.

